question is




Missing in Array
Difficulty: EasyAccuracy: 29.59%Submissions: 1.5MPoints: 2Average Time: 15m
You are given an array arr[] of size n - 1 that contains distinct integers in the range from 1 to n (inclusive). 
This array represents a permutation of the integers from 1 to n with one element missing. Your task is to identify and return the missing element.





solution is





class Solution {
  public:
    int missingNum(vector<int>& arr) {
        // code here
        int ans=0;

        for(auto ele: arr)

            ans ^= ele;

        for(int i=1;i<=arr.size()+1;i++)

            ans ^= i;

        return ans;
    }
};



